ompt_tokens": 7306, "total_tokens": 7306}, "id": "605675e5-c77a-916a-9758-8ef1fa7119f8"}, "input": {"input": ["# Diagnostic Methods for Mental Illnesses\n\nThis community revolves around various diagnostic methods and tests used in the assessment and diagnosis of mental illnesses. Key entities include 辅助检查 (Auxiliary Examinations), 体格检查 (Physical Examination), and 精神检查 (Mental State Examination), which are interconnected through their roles in providing comprehensive diagnostic information. The community highlights the importance of integrating physical, mental, and laboratory-based assessments to establish accurate diagnoses.\n\n## 辅助检查 (Auxiliary Examinations) as a central entity\n\n辅助检查 (Auxiliary Examinations) is the most central entity in this community, with a high degree of connectivity to other diagnostic methods. It encompasses a wide range of laboratory and imaging tests, such as blood tests, EEG, CT, MRI, and psychological assessments, which provide essential information for diagnosing and differentiating mental illnesses. Its relationships with other entities, such as 临床资料分析 (Clinical Data Analysis) and 心理测验 (Psychological Tests), underscore its pivotal role in the diagnostic process [Data: Entities (1266); Relationships (1438, 1439, 1440, 1443, 1444, +more)].\n\n## 体格检查 (Physical Examination) complements auxiliary tests\n\n体格检查 (Physical Examination) is a crucial component of the diagnostic process, working in tandem with auxiliary examinations to provide a comprehensive assessment of a patient's health. It involves systematic physical checks for inpatients and focused examinations for outpatients based on their medical history. Its relationship with 辅助检查 (Auxiliary Examinations) highlights the importance of integrating physical health assessments with laboratory and imaging tests for accurate diagnosis [Data: Entities (1265); Relationships (1435)].\n\n## 精神检查 (Mental State Examination) integrates with clinical data analysis\n\n精神检查 (Mental State Examination) is a key entity that involves conversation and observation to assess a patient's mental state, including consciousness, orientation, cognitive activities, and emotional activities. It integrates with 临床资料分析 (Clinical Data Analysis) to provide a holistic understanding of the patient's condition. This relationship emphasizes the need to combine mental state assessments with other clinical data for accurate diagnosis [Data: Entities (1264); Relationships (1434)].\n\n## 脑电图 (EEG) for assessing mental retardation\n\n脑电图 (EEG) is a specialized diagnostic method used to evaluate the etiology of mental retardation. Its relationship with 精神发育迟滞 (Mental Retardation) highlights its specific application in diagnosing developmental disorders. This targeted use of EEG underscores the importance of specialized tests in addressing specific mental health conditions [Data: Entities (1068); Relationships (1217)].\n\n## 头颅MRI (Head MRI) for detailed brain imaging\n\n头颅MRI (Head MRI) is a critical imaging test that provides detailed images of the brain, aiding in the diagnosis of mental illnesses. Its inclusion in 辅助检查 (Auxiliary Examinations) demonstrates the importance of advanced imaging techniques in understanding brain-related conditions. The relationship between these entities highlights the role of technology in modern mental health diagnostics [Data: Entities (1270); Relationships (1443)].", "# 性变态及其伴随疾病\n\n该社区以性变态为核心实体，围绕其展开的多种疾病如酒精中毒、颅脑外伤、老年性精神病、内分泌疾病和颞叶病变等，均可能与性变态伴随发生。这些实体通过高强度的关系相互连接，形成了一个以性变态为中心的疾病网络。\n\n## 性变态作为核心实体\n\n性变态是该社区的核心实体，所有其他疾病实体都与其有直接关系。性变态的高度数（7）表明其在网络中的中心地位，可能对个体行为和社会产生重要影响。这种中心性使得性变态成为理解该社区动态的关键。 [Data: Entities (2464), Relationships (2894, 2895, 2898, 2899, 2900)]\n\n## 酒精中毒与性变态的关联\n\n酒精中毒与性变态之间存在高强度关系（combined_degree=8），表明两者可能伴随发生。这种关联可能对个体的健康和行为产生复合影响，增加了治疗和管理的复杂性。 [Data: Entities (2458), Relationships (2894)]\n\n## 颅脑外伤与性变态的关联\n\n颅脑外伤与性变态之间的关系强度同样为8，表明两者可能伴随发生。这种关联可能对个体的神经系统和行为产生深远影响，需要综合治疗和干预。 [Data: Entities (2459), Relationships (2895)]\n\n## 老