re [Data: Entities (587); Relationships (664, 662)].\n\n## Violent behavior is another critical concern in psychiatric care\n\nViolent behavior is a high-risk event that nurses must monitor and prevent through various interventions, such as communication, psychological care, and behavioral interventions. The relationship between violent and suicidal behaviors underscores the importance of addressing multiple high-risk factors in psychiatric care to ensure patient safety and well-being [Data: Entities (586); Relationships (662)].\n\n## Doctors rely on nursing records for accurate diagnoses\n\nDoctors, as medical professionals, rely on nursing records to gain valuable insights into a patient's condition and medical history. This collaborative approach enhances the quality of care delivered to patients, particularly those with mental health conditions. The relationship between doctors and nursing records highlights the importance of teamwork and communication in healthcare [Data: Entities (549, 555); Relationships (617)].\n\n## Psychiatric care aims to provide holistic support\n\nPsychiatric care encompasses the comprehensive treatment and management of patients with mental health conditions. This includes a range of approaches such as observation, therapy, and medication to address various mental health issues. A critical aspect of psychiatric care is the prevention and management of violent and suicidal behaviors in patients, ensuring their safety and well-being. The role of nurses in providing psychiatric care is essential to achieving these goals [Data: Entities (551); Relationships (615)].", "# Mental Health Care and Patient Management Community\n\nThis community is centered around the comprehensive care and management of patients with mental health conditions, primarily within a hospital environment. Key entities include MENTAL HEALTH CARE, PATIENT, and MEDICAL STAFF, which are interconnected through various relationships that highlight the care, monitoring, and support provided to patients. The community also involves specific areas within the hospital, such as the WARD, ISOLATION ROOM, and ACTIVITY ROOM, which are designed to meet the diverse needs of patients. The relationships between these entities emphasize the holistic approach to mental health care, addressing both physical and psychological well-being.\n\n## Comprehensive mental health care for patients\n\nMENTAL HEALTH CARE is a central entity in this community, encompassing the comprehensive care and management of patients with mental health conditions. This process includes monitoring, psychological support, and safety measures to ensure the well-being of individuals. The goal is to address the needs of patients through a holistic approach that integrates various aspects of care to promote mental health and stability. The relationship between PATIENT and MENTAL HEALTH CARE highlights the primary focus on providing tailored interventions and support to those with mental health conditions [Data: Entities (546, 545), Relationships (609, 694)].\n\n## Patient management in a hospital environment\n\nThe hospital environment plays a significant role in shaping the experiences and outcomes of patients. It can have a notable impact on their mental health, potentially influencing their emotional well-being and psychological state. Additionally, the hospital environment can affect patient behavior, including actions such as attempts to leave without authorization. The WARD, ISOLATION ROOM, and ACTIVITY ROOM are specific areas within the hospital designed to meet the diverse needs of patients, ensuring their safety and well-being [Data: Entities (557, 558, 563), Relationships (629, 630, 671)].\n\n## Medical staff's critical role in patient care\n\nThe MEDICAL STAFF comprises healthcare professionals who play a critical role in providing emergency care, monitoring patients, and ensuring the safety and security of the hospital environment. This group includes nurses and other